Separate — required modules & notes
Standard library modules (no install needed)

argparse — CLI parsing

socket — TCP connect + banner grabbing

concurrent.futures — ThreadPoolExecutor for parallel scanning

ipaddress — parse CIDR networks

time, sys — utility functions

Optional / external modules (install if you want ARP discovery)

scapy — for ARP-based local host discovery.

Install: pip install scapy (or pip3 install scapy)

Run ARP discovery as root/administrator (e.g., sudo python3 network_scanner.py --cidr 192.168.1.0/24) because scapy uses raw sockets / packet send.

Quick install commands

If you only need the basic scanner (no ARP): nothing to install.

If you want ARP discovery:

pip3 install scapy

On many systems you must run the script with sudo (Linux/macOS) or Administrator privileges (Windows).

Short usage examples

Scan local network (requires scapy + root):
sudo python3 network_scanner.py --cidr 192.168.1.0/24 --ports 22,80,443

Scan single host for common ports:
python3 network_scanner.py --host 10.0.0.5 --ports 1-1024

Faster scanning with more threads (be careful — noise):
python3 network_scanner.py --host 10.0.0.5 --ports 1-1024 --workers 400 --timeout 0.5
